CII.JK", "IKAN.JK", "SCPI.JK", "PRIM.JK", "BEER.JK", "MTLA.JK", "POSA.JK", "TRIO.JK", "PEGE.JK", "INCI.JK", "SEMA.JK", "TNCA.JK", "GTSI.JK", "PEVE.JK", "TRIL.JK", "PNSE.JK", "IOTF.JK", "MRAT.JK", "ARKA.JK", "CHIP.JK", "YELO.JK", "PORT.JK", "MAGP.JK", "HADE.JK", "IBOS.JK", "TIRA.JK", "PSDN.JK", "MAPB.JK", "ASJT.JK", "BIPP.JK", "CTBN.JK", "VOKS.JK", "SONA.JK", "VKTR.JK", "BSML.JK", "RELF.JK", "LMPI.JK", "NEST.JK", "KBAG.JK", "DEPO.JK", "IPPE.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-13T15:08:44", "title": "PT Siantar Top Expands into US Market to Boost Export Sales Potential"}, {"body": "PT Bank Pembangunan Daerah Jawa Timur Tbk (BJTM) has allocated IDR 200 billion in capital to regional banks in Southeast Sulawesi and East Nusa Tenggara, which is expected to boost the banks' core capital and expand services, ultimately increasing revenue. In 2023, BJTM reported a net profit of IDR 1.47 trillion, down from IDR 1.54 trillion in 2022, but its stock price has increased by IDR 40 since June 2024, from IDR 510 to IDR 550 per share.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51739/official-bjtm-injects-capital-regional-banks", "sub_sector": ["banks"], "tags": ["IDX", "Earnings Report", "Financial Ratios", "Balance Sheets", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["BJTM.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-13T14:11:08", "title": "PT Bank Pembangunan Daerah Jawa Timur Allocates IDR 200 Billion to Regional Banks in Southeast Sulawesi and East Nusa Tenggara."}, {"body": "PT Multistrada Arah Sarana TBK (MASA) has set a buyback price of IDR 8,400 per share, a 95.5% increase from the highest average price in the 12 months prior to its suspension in July 2024. The company will hold its third extraordinary general meeting of shareholders next Wednesday, following two previous failed attempts, as part of its go-private plan, with SocGen SA Compagnie Generale des Etablissments Michelin holding a 99.64% stake in MASA.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "consumer-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51738/private-masa-sets-exercise-price-idr", "sub_sector": ["automobiles-components"], "tags": ["Buyback", "Executive Changes", "IDX", "Market Sentiment", "Dividends", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["MASA.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-13T10:55:57", "title": "PT Multistrada Arah Sarana sets buyback price at IDR 8,400 per share as part of go-private plan."}, {"body": "PT Murni Sadar Tbk (MTMH) secured a IDR 50 billion working capital credit from PT Bank Mandiri Tbk (BMRI) to pay claims to the Healthcare Social Security Agency, with the facility consisting of IDR 30 billion in receivable financing and IDR 20 billion in revolving general switchable RF. The credit, which has a floating interest rate of 7.75% per annum, will be available for one year and is secured by collateral including receivables, building rights, and fixed assets.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "healthcare", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51737/covering-bpjs-kesehatan-bills-rs-murni-teguh-seeks-loan", "sub_sector": ["healthcare-equipment-providers", "banks"], "tags": ["Interest Rates", "Debt", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["MTMH.JK", "BMRI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-13T10:26:59", "title": "Murni Teguh Hospitals secures IDR 50 billion working capital credit from Bank Mandiri to pay healthcare social security agency claims."}, {"body": "Foreign investors sold a net 120.10 million shares on Thursday, December 12, with PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia (BBRI) and PT Bank Mandiri (BMRI) being the top sell list, with net volumes of -145.42 million shares and -38.34 million shares, respectively. Meanwhile, PT Astrindo Nusantara Infrastruktur (TICKER) and PT Goto Gojek Tokopedia (TICKER) were the top buy list, with net volumes of 129.47 million shares and 126.23 million shares, respectively.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51730/foreign-transactions-decreased-foreign-volume-shares", "sub_sector": ["banks", "banks", "oil-gas-coal", "software-it-services"], "tags": ["Foreign Investor", "IDX", "Bearish"], "tickers": ["BBRI.JK", "BMRI.JK", "BIPI.JK", "GOTO.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-12T18:04:18", "title": "Foreign investors in Jakarta's market show net selling of 120.10 million shares on Thursday, December 12."}, {"body": "PT Astra Nusantara Infrastruktur TBK (Bipi) reclaimed the top spot in the net foreign category, with a net foreign purchase of 129.47 million shares, resulting from foreign buy of 134.26 million shares and foreign sell of 4.79 million shares. Meanwhile, PT Goto Gojek Tokopedia TBK (Goto) saw a decline in net foreign volume to 126.23 million shares, with a stock price fluctuation that closed at IDR 77 per share.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "technology", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51729/bipi-goto-swap-foreign", "sub_sector": ["software-it-services"], "tags": ["IDX", "Foreign Investor", "Market Trends", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["GOTO.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-12T17:38:11", "title": "PT Astrindo Nusantara Infrastruktur Reclaims Top Spot in Net Foreign Category on Indonesian Stock Exchange."}, {"body": "PT Buana Lintas Laut TBK (BULL) expects its net profit margin to increase in Q4 2024 due to higher vessel charter tariffs, which will improve its gross profit margin. The company's net profit margin was 12.28% in Q3 2024, down from 22.73% in Q3 2023, but its stock performance has been bullish throughout the year, with a 19.41% increase since the beginning of the year to IDR 123 per share.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51723/bull-confident-profit-margin-increasing-year-end", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["IDX", "Bullish", "Earnings Report", "Market Trends", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["BULL.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-12T10:22:19", "title": "PT Buana Lintas Laut TBK Expects Higher Net Profit Margin in Q4 2024 Due to Increased Vessel Charter Tariffs."}, {"body": "Foreign investors acquired 63.83 million shares of PT XL Axiata Tbk (EXCL) yesterday, despite a 2.18% price correction, resulting in a net foreign buy of 35.13 million shares. This comes after EXCL finalized a merger agreement with PT Smartfren Telecom Tbk, which will result in a rebranded entity with an enterprise value of IDR 104 trillion, and announced a share buyback plan for minority shareholders opposing the merger.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 1, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "infrastructures", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51722/price-shrank-foreign-investors-rake-excls-shares", "sub_sector": ["telecommunication", "telecommunication"], "tags": ["Mergers & Acquisitions", "Buyback", "Foreign Investor", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["EXCL.JK", "FREN.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-12T10:16:58", "title": "Foreign investors acquire millions of shares of PT XL Axiata despite stock price dip."}, {"body": "PT XL Axiata Tbk (EXCL) and PT Smartfren Telecom Tbk (FREN) are offering a buyback option to minority shareholders, allocating IDR 3.09 trillion to repurchase up to 10% of outstanding shares at IDR 2,350 per share and IDR 25 per share, respectively. The merged entity, PT XLSmart Telecom Sejahtera Tbk, is projected to have a pre-synergy enterprise value of over IDR 104 trillion (approximately USD 6.5 billion), with Axiata Sinarmas holding equal portions of shares alongside public investors who will retain 30.4% of shares.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "infrastructures", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51721/disapprove-merger-excl-fren-offer-buyback", "sub_sector": ["telecommunication", "telecommunication"], "tags": ["Buyback", "Mergers & Acquisitions", "IDX", "Executive Changes", "Market Trends", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["EXCL.JK", "FREN.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-12T08:45:24", "title": "Axiata and Smartfren offer minority shareholders buyback option ahead of merger."}, {"body": "PT Humpuss Intermoda Transportasi Tbk (HITS) divested one of its oil tanker units to PT Hutama Trans Kencana for USD 2.97 million, aiming to optimize its oil transport business segment and improve asset management. As of September 2024, HITS reported USD 788 million in cash and cash equivalents, and a total equity of USD 1.71 billion, with its market capitalization increasing by 14.13% to IDR 2.98 trillion.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51720/optimising-assets-hits-sold-oil-tanker", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["Mergers & Acquisitions", "Balance Sheets", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["HITS.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-12T08:02:47", "title": "Humpuss Intermoda Transportasi sells one of its oil tanker units to affiliate company for USD 2.97 million."}, {"body": "The Jakarta Composite Stock Price Index rose 0.15% or 11.47 points to 7,464.75, driven by a 3.50% increase in PT Bayan Resources Tbk (BYAN) shares, which contributed 10.16 points to the index's gain. Foreign investors recorded a net purchase of IDR 495.42 billion (USD 31.15 million), significantly higher than the previous day's IDR 84.26 billion (USD 5.31 million), with a total trading volume of 26.48 billion shares and transaction value of IDR 16.29 trillion.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 1, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51719/jci-soars-foreign-investors-increased-spending", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["IDX Composite", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Foreign Investor", "Market Sentiment", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["BYAN.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-11T19:53:31", "title": "Jakarta Composite Stock Price Index Rises for Third Consecutive Day"}, {"body": "According to a retail sales survey by Bank Indonesia, the price expectation index is projected to rise to 157.8 in January 2025 before declining to 165.4 in April 2025, driven by seasonal factors such as rainfall and holiday demand normalisation. Retail sales are expected to decrease to 144.7 in January 2025 and 146.5 in April 2025, down from 163.9 in December 2024 and 156.5 in March 2025, respectively.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51713/survey-expects-inflation-increase-january", "sub_sector": ["banks", "banks", "banks", "banks"], "tags": ["Inflation", "Retail Sales", "Economic Reports", "Bearish"], "tickers": ["BBHI.JK", "BNII.JK", "MCOR.JK", "BBSI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-11T15:02:39", "title": "Indonesian inflation expected to rise in January 2025 before declining in April 2025 due to seasonal factors."}, {"body": "Fore Coffee plans to open 216 outlets across 43 cities in Indonesia, driven by the promising prospects of the coffee industry, with coffee consumption expected to increase by 4.8 million bags in 2024/2025, according to the United States Department of Agriculture report. The company's digital platform, launched in 2018, has been downloaded by millions of users, providing a personal and interactive experience for customers, and aims to capitalize on the low per capita coffee consumption in Indonesia, which stands at 1 kilogram per year.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 2, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 65, "sector": "consumer-non-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51701/prospects-indonesian-coffee-industry-promising-fore-outlets-cities", "sub_sector": ["food-beverage"], "tags": ["Market Trends", "Retail Sales", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-12-10T14:41:42", "title": "Fore Coffee Expands to 216 Outlets Across 43 Cities in Indonesia Amid Growing Coffee Consumption."}]